Version: 2.3.1 Build:build-482 2010-05-27

Create a new crucible entry. In objectives, type something like {noformat}this is a 'test'{noformat} Save it.

Close and reopen your browser and go back to the crucible entry that you just created.

Edit the objective. Note that it now says:

{noformat}this is a &#039;test&#039;{noformat}

Add "2" at the end of the objective. Save it. 

Now the objective literally reads:

{noformat}this is a &#039;test&#039;2{noformat}

Similar bad replacements happen with literal ampersands. They become {noformat}&amp;{noformat}. If you edit the objectives and save it, that becomes something like {noformat}&amp;amp;{noformat}
